The defendant Travis Elroy Lamphier was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Travis Elroy Lamphier is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

1:04 PM Prosecuting attorney Chad C La Lor in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Travis Elroy Lamphier in court, in custody.  Attorney Michael Charles Hoffman in court for Travis Elroy Lamphier. Court calls case. State indicates that the defendant will plead to count 1 with the repeater enhancer, dismiss remaining all remaining counts. 1 year of County Jail stayed for 2 years of probation; 0 days served with 0 days credit, DOC programming, $50 fine plus costs and surcharges. If revoked, the jail sentence would be consecutive to any other cases. The defendant is currently serving a sentence in case 21CF501. Attorney Hoffman agrees. 
Defendant pleads no contest. Court reviews firearms restriction for felons. Court accepts the plea, finds that the plea has been knowingly and voluntarily made and finds the defendant guilty. Court dismisses counts 2 and 3.  
On count 1, the Court orders 1 year jail consecutive to any other sentences including 21CF501, impose and stayed for 2 years of probation; conditions of 0 days served with 0 days credit, DOC programming, $50 fine plus costs and surcharges with 120 days to pay.
